    <td>When using WebDAV for a particular blobstore, it can be configured with a <code>webdav_config</code> hash. Perform the following steps:<br/><br/>
      1. Replace <code>WEBDAV_BASIC_AUTH_USER</code> and <code>WEBDAV_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD</code> with Basic AUTH credentials that Cloud Controller can use to talk your WebDAV installation.<br/><br/>
      2. Replace <code>WEBDAV_SECRET</code> with a secret phrase used to sign URLs.<br/><br/>
      3. Replace <code>WEBDAV_CERT</code>, <code>WEBDAV_PRIVATE_KEY</code>, and <code>WEBDAV_CA_CERT_BUNDLE</code> with proper TLS configuration that will be used for the internal blobstore.<br/><br/>
      4. Replace <code>WEBDAV_PUBLIC_ENDPOINT</code> with the public URL (e.g. `https://blobstore.SYSTEM_DOMAIN`) that resolves to your WebDAV installation.<br/><br/>
      5. Replace <code>WEBDAV_PRIVATE_ENDPOINT</code> with a URL routable on your internal network. This will default to `https://blobstore.service.cf.internal` if not set.<br/><br/>
      6. Replace <code>WEBDAV_BASIC_AUTH_USER</code> and <code>WEBDAV_BASIC_AUTH_PASSWORD</code> with Basic AUTH credentials that Cloud Controller can use to talk your WebDAV installation.
